HEADWORD: Grammalogue
<hw>Gram"ma*logue</hw> <pr>(gr⟦acr⟧m"m⟦adot⟧*l⟦ocr⟧g)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>gra`mma</grk> letter + <grk>lo`gos</grk>
word. Cf. <er>Logogram</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Phonography)</fld>
<def>Literally, a <it>letter word</it>; a word represented by a
logogram; as, <examp>it</examp>, represented by |, that is,
<it>t</it>.</def> <rj><au>Pitman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

